    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-04-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-04-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="339"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/1063: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 8, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. Your No. 81. The Treasury has been consulted in regard to possible
                    arrangement suggested by the Director of Exchange, and has suggested the
                    following reply. For your information this is regarded as the most feasible and
                    easily effected arrangement, though alternative arrangements may be
                    possible.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Please refer to letter from Secretary Morgenthau to Minister of Finance
                        Souza Costa dated July 15, 1937 and delivered to latter on that date. Under
                        terms of this letter<note n="20" xml:id="d339fn20">See Treasury Department
                            press release No. 10–78, July 15, 1937, <hi rend="italic"
                            >infra</hi>.</note> U. S. Treasury will through Federal Reserve Bank of
                        New York as its fiscal agent make available dollar exchange up to 60 million
                        dollars at annual rate of interest ½ of one per cent above average Federal
                        Reserve Bank of New York rediscount rate. At present effective rate is 1% or
                        total cost of credit one and one-half per cent per annum. Transaction which
                        you describe is eligible under terms of letter of July 15, 1937.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
